title: After Win, 'Dogs Stay No. 25 in AFCA Poll
text:
After Win, 'Dogs Stay No. 25 in AFCA Poll 
By Zach Schneider After Win, 'Dogs Stay No. 25 in AFCA Poll October 5, 2015 Updated Oct 5, 2015 at 5:55 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) football team stayed ranked No. 25 for the third straight week in the latest American Football Coaches' Association (AFCA) Division II poll, which was released on Monday afternoon. 
Earlier this season, the Bulldogs last week were knocked out of the nation's top 15 for the first time since the 2008 season. The team failed to gain any ground the past two weeks despite wins over Upper Iowa and MSU-Moorhead.
